Remove the NO-IR flag from the US 6 GHz regulatory rule.

On this tree, wireless-regdb is still converted by dbparse.py which only
supports the older flag set and cannot encode finer grained 6 GHz AP
exceptions such as VLP-only beaconing. In practice this leaves all US
6 GHz channels unusable for AP mode on mt7996, while countries such as
JP and KR work because their 6 GHz entries do not carry NO-IR.

For this local target, prefer enabling US 6 GHz AP operation by dropping
the blanket NO-IR restriction on the 5925-7125 MHz rule.
---
--- a/db.txt
+++ b/db.txt
@@ -2052,7 +2052,7 @@ country US: DFS-FCC
 	(5850 - 5895 @ 40), (27), NO-OUTDOOR, AUTO-BW, NO-IR
 	# 6g band
 	# https://www.federalregister.gov/documents/2020/05/26/2020-11236/unlicensed-use-of-the-6ghz-band
-	(5925 - 7125 @ 320), (12), NO-OUTDOOR, NO-IR
+	(5925 - 7125 @ 320), (12), NO-OUTDOOR
 	# 60g band
 	# reference: section IV-D https://docs.fcc.gov/public/attachments/FCC-16-89A1.pdf
 	# channels 1-6 EIRP=40dBm(43dBm peak)
